      "writtenOn": "2019-10-09T22:52:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, there was a thread about this earlier.\n\nIt appears that in /practice/, neither Chan nor I have seen cases in which this is not an index (\\d). In theory, it looks like this can in fact be an alphabetical string if the user provides a name generator [1], [2]; it\u0027s the default generator that provides a numerical index [3]\n\nI understand this is not entirely along the lines of param/index that is to be part of Chrome test ID, but I have not yet found evidence of how Chrome is using gtest that guarantees no name generator provided.\n\n[1] https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/googletest/src/googletest/include/gtest/internal/gtest-internal.h?l\u003d707\u0026rcl\u003df2fb48c3b3d79a75a88a99fba6576b25d42ec528\n[2] https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/googletest/src/googletest/include/gtest/internal/gtest-internal.h?l\u003d655\u0026rcl\u003df2fb48c3b3d79a75a88a99fba6576b25d42ec528\n[3] https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/googletest/src/googletest/include/gtest/gtest-message.h?l\u003d209\u0026rcl\u003df2fb48c3b3d79a75a88a99fba6576b25d42ec528",
      "parentUuid": "0e4ee851_c637e0f4",
